<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pianist Murray Perahia flew from London to
accept an award as classical recording artist of the year in the
second Mumm Champagne Classical Music Awards at Avery Fisher Hall
in Lincoln Center.
   Conductor Sir Georg Solti was honored at Monday night's ceremony
for record of the year for Wagner's ``Lohengrin.''
   Perahia received his award for his recording of Beethoven's
