<HEAD>Bush Wins Backing of Washington Times</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Washington Times endorsed Republican
presidential contender George Bush, saying the vice president and
Sen. Dan Quayle are ``more likely to promote continued economic
growth and strategic strength.''
   The newspaper praised Bush as the candidate who would ``best
help the United States build upon the prosperity of the 1980s while
preparing for the challenges of the 21st century.''
   The Times also criticized Democratic nominee Michael Dukakis,
who it said ``talks about bedrock values but doesn't seem to
understand them. His policies reflect a genuine distrust of the
values that most Americans hold dear.''
