<HEAD>Two Soldiers Killed, 4 Hurt In Army Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An armored personnel carrier on a
training exercise rolled over today, killing two Australian
soldiers and injuring the other four in the vehicle, the army said.
   The accident happened at the Puckapunyal Army base, about 60
miles north of Melbourne, said army spokesman Maj. Mike Hansen.
   He said one instructor and five students were taking part in a
driver-training course in the M113 carrier when it rolled over in
rough terrain on the training range.
   The injured were rushed to the army base military hospital while
state coroner Hal Hallenstein ordered an inquiry into the accident.
   There was no immediate word on the condition of the injured
soldiers, whom Hansen said were ``all male, and very young.''
</TEXT>
