<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0423</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow, Rain Hit Great Lakes Region</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Light snow and rain fell in the Great Lakes region early today
but most of the rest of the country was dry.
   Cold air flowing across warm lake waters generated snow and rain
south of most of the Great Lakes. Snow and rain fell in northeast
Ohio, western New York state and lower Michigan. Snow also fell in
upper Michigan south of Lake Superior.
   Elsewhere, light rain was scattered over northeast Nebraska and
Florida. There was light rain and fog in Maine, and dense fog along
the northern California coast reduced visibility to an eighth of a
mile at Arcata and Eureka. Fog also formed along the southern
California coast.
   The rest of the country was mostly dry.
   Today's forecast called for brisk northwest winds to produce
snow along the eastern shores of the Great Lakes. Scattered rain
was predicted for northern New England and the northern and central
Appalachians, as well as Washington state and parts of Oregon.
   Highs were forecast to be in the 30s in upper Michigan, northern
Wisconsin, Minnesota and North Dakota; in the 40s and 50s from New
England and the Great Lakes through the central Appalachians and
the central Plains to the northern Rockies and Washington state; in
the 80s in the southern halves of Florida and Texas; and from 85 to
95 degrees in the desert Southwest and the inland valleys of
California. Highs elsewhere were forecast to be in the 60s and 70s.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 18 degrees at Devils
Lake, N.D., to 78 degrees at Corpus Christi, Texas, Naval Air
Station.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 46 fair; Boston 46 fair; Buffalo 39 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 54 fair; Cincinnati 36 fair; Cleveland 36 foggy;
Detroit 39 cloudy; Miami 71 fair; New York 49 partly cloudy;
Philadelphia 46 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 36 cloudy; Portland,
Maine 46 foggy; Washington 44 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 34 fair; Chicago 31 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
62 fair; Denver 42 fair; Des Moines 38 fair; Indianapolis 36
cloudy; Kansas City 50 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 31 fair;
Nashville 39 fair; New Orleans 54 fair; St. Louis 51 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 54 partly cloudy; Anchorage 27 partly cloudy;
Las Vegas 64 fair; Los Angeles 61 foggy; Phoenix 76 fair; Salt Lake
City 44 fair; San Diego 64 foggy; San Francisco 52 cloudy; Seattle
46 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 39 fair; Toronto 41 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
