<HEAD>Boa Constrictor Greets Cornell Cornerback in Shower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hours after his team drubbed Dartmouth,
Cornell University cornerback Evan Parke met yet another muscular,
6-foot opponent last weekend, this one in his shower.
   A Bahamian boa constrictor gave Parke, 20, a rude homecoming
when he returned home early Sunday morning, a day after Cornell
beat Dartmouth 24-7.
   Parke said he had just stepped into the shower he saw the snake
curled around the shower head.
   ``I didn't need to look twice,'' he said. ``The snake freaked me
out. I jumped back and picked up my towel. I left the water on. I
didn't want to look at it.''
   Gordon Gabaree, a private wildlife control specialist, extracted
the boa from the shower. The snake is believed to belong to a
former tenant who reported a snake missing two months ago.
