<1ST_LINE>d a PM-TielessTeacher     10-25 0194</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Tieless Teacher,0200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teacher Suspended For Classroom Appearance Returns Without Tie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POINT PLEASANT, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school geometry teacher
suspended for 11 days for wearing jeans and no tie returned to work
today in the same outfit.
   In jeans and a shirt without a tie, Bill Webb showed up to teach
at Point Pleasant High School this morning, according to County
Schools Superintendent Charles Chambers. Chambers said no immediate
action was taken.
   Chambers issued a dress code this year for county school
teachers that bans jeans and requires men to wear neckties.
   The superintendent suspended Webb, 46, without pay Oct. 7. Webb
had just finished a four-day suspension over his refusal to ditch
his jeans and don a tie.
   The Mason County Board of Education upheld the latest suspension
Monday night, and directed Webb to report to work this morning in
proper dress.
   ``I will either get a letter, if they follow the same process
that they have, or there is the possibility that I will be
suspended at the end of the day,'' Webb said. ``I guess there's
even the possibility that they may not let me complete the day.''
</TEXT>
