<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--MissingFreighter     10-25 0097</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Missing Freighter,0098</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Abandon Search for Freighter with 9 Aboard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The two-week search for a
freighter carrying nine crewmembers and 240 tons of logs has been
called off, the Marine Department said Tuesday.
   The 600-ton MV Sin Hoon Hing left Kuala Baram Oct. 7,
encountered bad weather, and failed to arrive as scheduled on Oct.
9 in Kuching, about 540 miles south of Kuala Lumpur.
   Searches by the Marine Department and one launched by Ting Ing
Fong, the owner of the vessel, were abandoned, said marine officer
David Fu Jee Foh.
</TEXT>
