<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Spain     10-25 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Iran-Spain,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Spain, Iran to Cooperate in Reconstruction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spain and Iran have agreed to cooperate in
rebuilding industries destroyed in the 8-year-old war between Iran
and Iraq, the official Islamic Republic News Agency said.
   Spain's industry and energy minister, Claudi Aranzadi, and
Iranian Energy Minister Bijan Namdar Anganeh met in Tehran on Monday
and agreed to a joint project to reconstruct two power plants,
according to the agency.
   The two countries also will construct a cement factory in the
southern Hormuzgan province, according to the agency, monitored in
Nicosia.
   Aranzadi said he hoped Spain also would provide Iran the
technology for manufacturing pharmaceutical products, the agency
said.
   Spain did not participate in various sanctions imposed on Iran
after the rise of the Islamic Revolution in 1979.
</TEXT>
