<HEAD>Peasants Discover Dinosaur Skeleton</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peasants in southwestern China discovered a
29-foot-long dinosaur skeleton after a rainstorm washed away soil,
the official Xinhua News Agency said Tuesday.
   The 11{-foot skeleton, which was well-preserved, was found in
Yunnan province this month and excavated by archaeologists. The
remains have not been identified or dated, Xinhua said.
