<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Nigeria-Airline     10-25 0122</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nigeria-Airline,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nigeria Airways Cuts Service to 6 African Countries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nigeria Airways, the national carrier of
Africa's most populous nation, stopped service to six African
nations and is cutting its staff, the airline announced Tuesday.
   The airline said it was operating only a handful of planes after
its Airbus jetliners were seized by France for nonpayment of bills,
and several other planes were damaged in accidents.
   The airline has canceled flights to Benin, Sierra Leone, Zaire,
Equatorial Guinea, Kenya and Togo. Flights to Liberia, Ivory Coast,
Gambia, Senegal and Cameroon will continue, but staff will be cut by
60 percent.
   A third of the staff in New York and 65 percent in London also
will be cut.
</TEXT>
