<HEAD>Naphtha Tank Fire on Merlimau Island</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SINGAPORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A naphtha tank caught fire Tuesday on Merlimau
Island but the blaze was brought under control after three hours and
no one was injured, officials said.
   The 120,000-barrel tank at the Singapore Refining Co. Pte. Lt.
continued to burn, however, and precautions were taken to keep the
fire from spreading to other tanks, said a company official who
asked not to be identified.
   The cause of the fire on the island off the west coast of
Singapore was unknown.
