<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Ryan'sHope     10-25 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Ryan's Hope,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>ABC Cancels `Ryan's Hope'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The daytime drama ``Ryan's Hope'' has been
canceled after 13{ years, because too many affiliates pre-empt the
noontime soap opera for local newscasts, ABC announced Tuesday.
   The series will have its last broadcast on Jan. 13.
   ```Ryan's Hope' has not been rejected by the audience, it has
simply been unavailable to viewers'' because of pre-emptions, said
Jo Ann Emmerich, vice president of daytime programs for ABC
Entertainment. ``Without sufficient stations to carry it, it has
become a victim of audience erosion.''
   At its lowest ebb, the show was carried by only 75 percent of
ABC's affiliates. ABC elected not to move it because there was no
appropriate timeslot for a half-hour drama.
   The series is set in New York and follows the exploits of an
Irish-Catholic family. It has won 17 Daytime Emmys and 11 Writers
Guild awards.
   ABC said a replacement program would be announced soon.
</TEXT>
