<HEAD>Tieless Teacher Is Reprimanded; Meeting With Superintendent Next</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POINT PLEASANT, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school math teacher who
refuses to ditch his blue jeans and wear a necktie was reprimanded
Tuesday and ordered to comply with the dress code.
   Bill Webb, a 20-year veteran of teaching, already has been
suspended for 15 days this year. He refuses to obey a new dress code
for teachers at Point Pleasant High School because he feels his
attire has nothing to do with how well he teaches. He also has said
the policy violates the law.
   Superintendent Charles Chambers suspended Webb, 46, without pay
Oct. 7. At the time, he had just finished a four-day suspension for
the same reason.
   The Mason County school board voted 5-0 Monday night to uphold
Webb's latest suspension.
   ``If he doesn't comply, I will set up a conference with the
superintendent,'' said principal Michael Whalen. ``That's the next
level. The superintendent will have a conference with him and, as in
the past, he'll also request (Webb) to comply with the rules.''
