<HEAD>Bush Has Nine-Point Lead In Maryland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican George Bush leads Democrat Michael
Dukakis 51 percent to 42 percent in Maryland, one of the most
Democratic states in the country and one that is considered
essential to Dukakis' electoral strategy, The Washington Post
reported in its Tuesday editions.
   The survey of 601 likely voters was conducted last Tuesday
through Saturday and had a margin of error of four percentage
points. Dukakis had double-digit leads in the state in the summer,
but the Post said he now suffers from high negative ratings _ 43
percent _ among Maryland voters.
