<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Xerox     10-25 0342</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Xerox,0354</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Xerox Earnings Up 9 Percent In Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Xerox Corp.'s third-quarter earnings rose
9 percent to $146 million, with a strong showing from the company's
financial services division, the company said Tuesday.
   Net income for the quarter ended Sept. 30 was up from $134
million in the comparable period last year. Per-share earnings were
up 12 percent to $1.37 from $1.23.
   Revenues in the third quarter rose 10 percent to $4.1 billion
from $3.8 billion last year, Xerox reported.
   ``Financial services continued to contribute to our earnings
growth, and business products and systems again reflected the
strong momentum shown in international operations all year,'' said
Xerox Chairman David T. Kearns.
   Net income for the first nine months of 1988 was $465 million,
an increase of 10 percent from $423 million in 1987. Earnings per
share were $4.33, an 11 percent increase from $3.92 in the previous
year. Nine-month revenues were $12 billion, up 10 percent from $11
billion last year.
   Xerox Financial Services Inc. contributed $78 million in
third-quarter net income, after allocated interest costs, a 13
percent gain from $69 million a year ago. In the nine-month period,
financial services contributed $246 million to Xerox income, also
up 13 percent from $218 million in the previous year's period.
   ``Our year-to-date earnings growth reflects gains in Crum and
Forster Inc.'s property and casualty and life insurance operations,
excellent growth at Xerox Credit Corp. and good performance in our
investment banking activities,'' said Melvin Howard, chairman of
Xerox Financial Services.
   Business products and systems contributed $68 million in
third-quarter earnings, up 5 percent from $65 million in the
year-ago period. Nine-month income was $219 million, up 7 percent
from $205 million a year ago.
   Xerox President Paul A. Allaire said the company continues to
experience good growth in copier-duplicator and printing products,
particularly in international operations.
   He said the new Xerox 50 Series copiers and duplicators are
being well received and will become available worldwide by the
first quarter of 1989, contributing significantly to 1989 earnings.
</TEXT>
