<2ND_LINE>AM-British Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares End Mixed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates throuoput with closing prices</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed mixed in uneventful trading
Tuesday on the London Stock Exchange.
   Traders were said to be looking toward Thursday's release of
British trade figures for September.
   ``I'd say it was a bit of calm before the storm,'' one market
maker said.
   He added that players were also awaiting Thursday's third-quarter
results for chemical giant Imperial Chemical Industries PLC which
are widely perceived as a barometer of British industry.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 0.6
point, or 0.03 percent, to 1,847.8.
   At its best, the index was up 1.2 points shortly after midday,
while losing as much as 8.4 points shortly after the start of
business.
   Volume was modest as just 373 million shares were traded,
compared with 464.5 million shares Monday.
</TEXT>
