<1ST_LINE>d f BC-Northwest-Flights     10-25 0110</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Northwest-Flights,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Northwest Airlines to Add Three Asian Flights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines announced that it will add three
nonstop Asian flights next year.
   Northwest said Tuesday that it will fly Boeing 747 jetliners
twice weekly between Tokyo and Saipan, in the Mariana Islands near
Guam, beginning April 1.
   The airline also will operate the jumbo jets three times weekly
between Tokyo and Minneapolis, and three times a week between Osaka,
in western Japan, and Los Angeles, both beginning June 3.
   Northwest, the fourth-largest U.S. airline, now operates nonstop
daily service from Tokyo to seven U.S. cities: Seattle, San
Francisco, Los Angeles, Chicago, Detroit, New York and Honolulu.
</TEXT>
