<HEAD>P&G Posts 12 Percent Profit Rise in First Fiscal Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Procter & Gamble Co. reported on Tuesday a
12 percent earnings increase and a 13 percent sales rise for its
fiscal first quarter.
   The consumer products giant said its earnings after taxes for the
three months ended Sept. 30 were $400 million, or $2.36 a share,
compared to $356 million, or $2.09 a share, in the comparable period
last year.
   First-quarter worldwide sales rose to $5.27 billion from $4.66
billion in last fiscal year.
   Procter & Gamble makes and markets a variety of cleaning and
personal care products, including Ivory soap and Cheer and Tide
laundry detergents, Crest toothpaste and Prell and Head and
Shoulders shampoos.
   It also makes food products such as Crisco shortening and Folgers
coffee.
