<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-KimberlyClark     10-25 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Kimberly Clark,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kimberly-Clark Third Quarter Profit Up 7.6 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kimberly-Clark Corp. on Tuesday reported its net
income rose by 7.6 percent in the third quarter from the same period
last year, aided by strong sales of disposable diapers.
   The Dallas-based manufacturer of Huggies diapers, Kleenex facial
tissue and other household and health care products, posted a profit
of $90.5 million, or $1.12 per share, compared with $84.1 million,
or 98 cents per share, in the year-earlier period.
   Sales during the three months ended Sept. 30 rose to $1.4 billion
from $1.2 billion a year earlier.
   Distribution of Huggies ``Supertrim'' diapers was completed
during the quarter and the company said sales volume reflected
completion of the rollout of the new product.
   For the nine-month period, net income rose to $283.9 million, or
$3.53 per share, from $243 million, or $2.74 per share, a year
earlier. Sales during the period rose to $4 billion from $3.63
billion.
   In addition to personal products, Kimberly-Clark produces
newsprint and business, correspondence and specialty papers.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
