<FILEID>AP-NR-10-25-88 2223EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>d f BC-China-Silk     10-25 0302</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-China-Silk,0312</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>China To Impose Export Tax on Silk</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China on Wednesday will begin levying export
tariffs of up to 100 percent on silk and its products to stop a
``silk cocoon war'' that has pushed up prices.
   The official Xinhua News Agency said the 100 percent tariff will
be levied on silkworm cocoon, raw silk, waste silk, silk yarn and
spun silk. Duties on silk, silk noil and fabrics made of waste silk
will be 80 percent, it said.
   The new duties, announced by the Customs Tariff Commission and
the General Administration of Customs, will affect all silk exports
regardless of when contracts were signed.
   China produces about 50,000 tons of cocoon silk annually, of
which 70 percent is for export. Ninety percent of raw silk and 40
percent of gray silk goods on international markets come from China,
according to the official China Daily.
   The Chinese government last month stated the China National Silk
Import and Export Corporation will undertake the unified handling of
silkworm cocoons, including exports, to halt the price war among
trading companies competing for scarce cocoons.
   It banned all other departments and individuals from purchasing
or handling silkworm cocoons and said Sino-foreign joint ventures
must apply for export permits in accordance with state-assigned
export quotas.
   Despite increasing demand for Chinese silk, cocoon production has
declined recently due to bad weather and low state-set prices.
Factories in Shanghai, Beijing and other cities have been forced to
stop production because of shortages of cocoons and filature silk.
   China Daily reported last week that Chinese silk traders were
turning down new customers at the Canton Trade Fair and there would
be a sharp drop in export contracts compared with previous fairs. It
said Chinese silk prices have risen by about 20 percent since last
spring.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
